    $( B&eacute;zout's identity:  For any integers ` A ` and ` B ` , there are
       integers ` x , y ` such that ` ( A gcd B ) = A x. x + B x. y ` .
       (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 22-Feb-2014.) $)
    bezout $p |- ( ( A e. ZZ /\ B e. ZZ ) ->
           E. x e. ZZ E. y e. ZZ ( A gcd B ) = ( ( A x. x ) + ( B x. y ) ) ) $=
      ( vz vu vv vt cz wcel cc0 wceq co cv cmul caddc wrex cn oveq2 eqeq2d cgcd
      wa wn crab clt ccnv csup weq eqeq1 2rexbidv oveq1d rexbidv oveq2d cbvrexv
      cr syl6bb cbvrabv simpll simplr eqid simpr bezoutlem4 elrab simprbi ex 0z
      syl 00id 0cn mul01i oveq12i gcd0val 3eqtr4ri mp3an oveq12 oveq1 oveqan12d
      rcla42ev eqeq12d mpbiri pm2.61d2 ) CIJZDIJZUBZCKLZDKLZUBZCDUAMZCANZOMZDBN
      ZOMZPMZLZBIQAIQZWDWGUCZWOWDWPUBZWHENZWMLZBIQAIQZERUDZJZWOWQFGHCDXAUOUEUFU
